(57, 1, '2013-12-05 11:46:25', '2013-12-05 11:46:25', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                 \r\nIf you’re the family member of an Australian citizen or permanent resident, you can join them in Australia on a family visa. Family members of eligible New Zealand citizens can also migrate to Australia on one of these popular visas.<br><br>\r\nYour relationship will determine which visa is right for you. If you’re not sure which visa you should apply for, get in touch with us today for your free visa assessment with Global-Migrate’s trained immigration advisors. We are the UK’s largest and most trusted Australian immigration consultancies, and can help you determine your immigration options.\r\n</p><h4>Partner (Spouse) Visas</h4>\r\nFor Australian immigration, partners include fiancés, married partners, and de facto partners, including those in same-sex relationship. A partner visa will allow you to enter and/or gain permanent residency in Australia. To find out if you are eligible for this type of visa, call our MARA certified consultants.\r\n<h4>Parent Visas</h4>\r\nIf you are the parent of an Australian citizen or permanent resident, or eligible New Zealand citizen, you can apply for a parent visa. This type of visa can give you permanent residency in Australia. If you want more details about how you or your parents can migrate to Australia, get in touch with us today to discuss visa options.\r\n\r\n<h4>Child Visas</h4>\r\nChildren of Australian citizens and permanent residents, and eligible New Zealand citizens, can also travel to and reside permanently in Australia. Child visas are available for dependent children, orphan relatives, and adopted children. Our visa advisors can help you apply for this type of visa, so get in touch today.<br><br>\r\nOther family v