(79, 1, '2013-12-05 11:56:59', '2013-12-05 11:56:59', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  Welcome to Global-Migrate, UK’s most trusted Australian Visa and Immigration consultancy. Our MARA regulated agent’s have a track record of successfully securing marriage or spouse visas for you and your spouse.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<a style="color:#003399" href="australia-visa-and-immigration.html">Australian immigration </a>under the spouse visa or marriage visa category is for applicants who are married to either a “Settled” Australian citizen, permanent resident or an eligible New Zealand citizen. At Global-Migrate we hire a dedicated team of regulated consultants to advise those who might be interested in migrating to Australia with their Australian Spouse or Partners. You could already be present in Australia and thinking of switching over to a this visa category or you might want to apply for this visa from the UK or any other part of the world, our specialist team can help you secure your visa.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nWith a 100% success rate with marriage visa applications and a No Visa No Fee policy we are sure to provide you with a service second to none.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nA partner visa application is closely scrutinised by the Department of Immigration and Citizenship. Success in the application is dependent on the quality of evidence of the relationship, hence why most of the applicants who contact us end up using our service as we guarantee them a strong submission of their application.\r\n\r\n</p><h4>Evidence of relationship</h4>\r\nThe couple applying for the partner visa need to provide documentation that demonstrates (for the 12 months prior to the date of lodging that they have a mutual commitment to a shared life together.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nEvidence of this shared life needs to be shown over a range of areas, from financial commitment to nature of the household to the social context of the relationship. Each partner must write a personal history statement that outlines their development and future intentions of the relationship. Many applicants fail due to showing insufficient or contradictory information.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nYou may apply for this visa if you are a Spouse or a Common-Law partner of an Australian Citizen.\r\n\r\n<h4>Duration</h4>\r\n\r\nA spouse partner visa or a defacto partner visa may initially be temporary, or permanent from the day of granting. The length of the relationship and children influences the partner visa subclass that applies. If the partner visa is initially temporary, the couple must show their ongoing relationship over the first two years to apply for a residency partner visa.\r\n\r\n<h4>How to apply?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe main applicant must be sponsored by an Australian citizen, permanent resident, or eligible New Zealand citizen. They must be able to provide evidence that they are legally married to the sponsor and in a ‘genuine, continuous relationship’ with them which they intend to continue after arrival in Australia.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nTo start your visa process you can contact us and speak to our highly qualified consultant’s for a no obligation free visa assessment\r\n\r\n<h4>Benefit of a Partner Visa?</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce granted, the applicant will have no restriction to work and reside in Australia.\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r