(116, 1, '2013-12-05 12:30:30', '2013-12-05 12:30:30', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p>\r\n                 Canada offers a program that allows immigrant investors to move to the country. The Immigrant Investor Program is currently on hold until further notice, although some investor visas are available through the Quebec Immigrant Investor Program.<br><br>\r\nApplications made before 1 July 2012 will still be processed, though. For these applications, you will need to show that you have suitable business experience along with sufficient funds to invest.<br><br>\r\nFor these applications, you will need a net worth of at least C$1,600,000, and make a C$800,000 investment. The investment is administered by Canadian immigration, and is used to improve the economy of the Canadian provinces.<br><br>\r\nOnce the investment is made, you will be granted a permanent residency visa. The original investment is returned to you, without interest, after around five years and three months. The processing time does vary, and Global-Migrate’s Canadian immigration consultants can give you the most up-to-date information.<br><br>\r\nAlthough this visa category is currently on hold, there are plenty of other ways for skilled business people to migrate to Canada. To find out about alternatives to the Investor visa, call, email, or request a call back from Global-Migrate today.<br><br>\r\nWe have years of experience helping people make their Canadian immigration dream a reality. Our free initial assessment can help determine the best visa choice for your individual circumstance. Get in touch today to get started!<br><br>\r\n\r\n					 </p>\r\n                   </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div cl