(137, 1, '2013-12-05 12:48:47', '2013-12-05 12:48:47', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>After successfully assisting thousands of applicants with their immigration queries, we have established ourselves as the most trusted and leading name in today''s UK immigration industry.</p>\r\n<p>We are proud to have clients who are happy with our high quality services. As We have a proven track record of thousands of successful visa applications and happy clients, our existing or previous client''s are always referring their friends or family to us, there making us believe we deliver what we promise. Our team of highly experienced, expert immigration consultants are familiar with today''s forever changing immigration regulations. We are proud to provide free assessment to all candidates who contact us. Complete our free assessment now which is quick and simple and let us take the stress on your behalf.</p>\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p>The UK Spouse Visa also referred to as the UK Marriage visa allows foreign nationals to settle in the UK with their settled Husband, Wife or Civil Partner. If they are not married or in a civil partnership, they may apply for a <a href="fiance-visa.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#2a52a4;">fiance visa</span></a> instead. A settled person is someone who either has <a href="british-citizenship.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;  color:#2a52a4;">British Citizenship</span></a> or permanent residency in the UK</p>\r\n<p>Before applying for a British Spouse visa you must read the following useful information;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Applications submitted on or before 8th July 2012:<br>\r\n</strong>If the application for a UK Marriage visa was submitted on or before the 8th of July 2012 the application will be considered if both the applicant and their sponsor i.e. husband, wife or civil partner were at least 18 years of age. Under this category of UK Visa, the applicant and/or their partner must also provide evidence that they are financially secure and have adequate accommodation.</p>\r\n<p>Upon approval of the application, the applicant will usually be given entry clearance or leave to remain for up to 27 months. On completion of this period the applicant may apply for settlement also known as <a href="indefinite-leave-to-remain.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;  color:#2a52a4;">Indefinite Leave to Remain</span></a> application.</p>\r\n<p>The applicant may include dependent children under the age of 18 on their application. The child may apply for .a British passport under the British Nationality Act of 1981.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Applications submitted on or after 9th July 2012:<br>\r\n</strong>The UK government implemented some changes to the UK Spouse visa application on the 9th of July 2012. As per the new legislation for their application to be considered for the UK visa the applicant and their spouse must be 18 years or older . If the application is successful, the applicant will usually be given an initial visa for a period of 30 months if they are applying for further leave to remain from within the UK or 33 months if they are applying for entry clearance from outside of the UK.</p>\r\n<p>Upon completion of this initial period the applicant will need to apply for an extension to their visa. They must provide evidence to demonstrate the genuineness and sustainability of their marriage. If successful, they will be granted with an extension of 30 months from within the UK. Once they complete a continuous period of five years in the UK they may apply for<a href="indefinite-leave-to-remain.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;  color:#2a52a4;"> settlement </span> </a>in the UK.</p>\r\n<p>The applicant may include dependent children under the age of 18 on their application. The child may apply for .a British passport under the British Nationality Act of 1981.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maintenance Requirement:</strong><br>\r\nApplicants applying under the new rules as off 9th July 2012 will need to provide evidence of maintenance requirement. The applicant or their settled UK partner must support the application with evidence that they can cover their living expenses without recourse to public funds for:</p>\r\n<p><em>27 months, if applying from outside the UK; or</em><br>\r\n<em> 2 years, if already in the UK and applying to switch from a different immigration category.</em></p>\r\n<p>Apart from the maintenance requirement, applicants will also need to meet other financial requirements. They must provide evidence that they have an income of at least £18,600. If they have one child dependent this amount will increase to £22,400. For any additional child dependents they will need to show availability of a further £2,400. They can meet the financial requirement by:</p>\r\n<p>income from employment or self employment of your themselves or their spouse/partner;<br>\r\ncertain income from sources other than employment, such as rent from property;<br>\r\nstate or private pensions of the applicant and/or their sponsor;<br>\r\ncash savings over a certain level</p>\r\n<h5></h5>\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p><strong>Age Eligibility criteria of UK Marriage Visa (Spouse Visa)</strong><br>\r\nTo qualify for a UK Marriage Visa, a prospective applicant must meet certain mandatory conditions pertaining to age and relationship status as mentioned above.</p>\r\n<p><strong>English Language Requirements;<br>\r\n</strong>As of the 29 November 2010 applicants applying for a UK spouse visa will be required to show that they have the required level of English to successfully integrate into the UK society. The new requirements will mean that marrying or married couples will be required to show that they can speak and understand basic English. This requirement is also applicable to those applying for fiancé visas as well as those applying for a UK visa as a same-sex couple. The following may be used as evidence;</p>\r\n<p><em>they are a national of the European Economic Area and Switzerland</em><br>\r\n<em> they are a national of a majority English Speaking Country</em><br>\r\n<em> they have passed an approved English Language test</em><br>\r\n<em> they hold a bachelors degree (or equiv.) that was taught in English</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits of UK marriage Visa<br>\r\n</strong>The UK Marriage Visa or Spouse Visa allows a non-EU individual to move to the UK and live with their UK settled partner. In order to have a successful outcome of the application all the immigration rules outlined for The UK Marriage Visa must be met. Applicants must make sure that all the relevant sections of the correct UK Spouse Visa application form are filled as applications may often be rejected due to many very small mistakes or grounds.</p>\r\n<p>Once the application is approved, the applicant can stay and work in the UK without the need for applying for a UK work permit. There are no restrictions on the type of employment undertaken by a Spouse Visa holder.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other important clauses one must take into consideration for a UK marriage visa are:</strong><br>\r\nProviding false information, forged documents or if any condition remains unfulfilled, Marriage Visa applications will be rejected immediately.</p>\r\n<p>Dependents of the applicant are also permitted entry in to the UK under this visa category.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What to do next?<br>\r\n</strong>To secure a UK Spouse Visa you must make the correct application and support it with the correct evidence. In recent years many applications have been refused over very small errors made during the application. This may effect your future applications. To avoid such unnecessary situations you must speak to our highly qualified UK Immigration Consultants in the first instance. You can do so by calling us on +44 (0)207 993 4762 or by checking your eligibility by completing the free online assessment below.</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left"> <a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'UK Spouse Visa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'uk-spouse-visa', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:53', '2014-11-14 16:20:53', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=137', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(138, 1, '2013-12-05 12:48:47', '2013-12-05 12:48:47', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>After successfully assisting thousands of applicants with their immigration queries, we have established ourselves as the most trusted and leading name in today''s UK immigration industry.</p>\r\n<p>We are proud to have clients who are happy with our high quality services. As We have a proven track record of thousands of successful visa applications and happy clients, our existing or previous client''s are always referring their friends or family to us, there making us believe we deliver what we promise. Our team of highly experienced, expert immigration consultants are familiar with today''s forever changing immigration regulations. We are proud to provide free assessment to all candidates who contact us. Complete our free assessment now which is quick and simple and let us take the stress on your behalf.</p>\r\n <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a>\r\n<p>The UK Spouse Visa also referred to as the UK Marriage visa allows foreign nationals to settle in the UK with their settled Husband, Wife or Civil Partner. If they are not married or in a civil partnership, they may apply for a <a href="fiance-visa.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#2a52a4;">fiance visa</span></a> instead. A settled person is someone who either has <a href="british-citizenship.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;  color:#2a52a4;">British Citizenship</span></a> or permanent residency in the UK</p>\r\n<p>Before applying for a British Spouse visa you must read the following useful information;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Applications submitted on or before 8th July 2012:<br>\r\n</strong>If the application for a UK Marriage visa was submitted on or before the 8th of July 2012 the application will be considered if both the applicant and their sponsor i.e. husband, wife or civil partner were at least 18 years of age. Under this category of UK Visa, the applicant and/or their partner must also provide evidence that they are financially secure and have adequate accommodation.</p>\r\n<p>Upon approval of the application, the applicant will usually be given entry clearance or leave to remain for up to 27 months. On completion of this period the applicant may apply for settlement also known as <a href="indefinite-leave-to-remain.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;  color:#2a52a4;">Indefinite Leave to Remain</span></a> application.</p>\r\n<p>The applicant may include dependent children under the age of 18 on their application. The child may apply for .a British passport under the British Nationality Act of 1981.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Applications submitted on or after 9th July 2012:<br>\r\n</strong>The UK government implemented some changes to the UK Spouse visa application on the 9th of July 2012. As per the new legislation for their application to be considered for the UK visa the applicant and their spouse must be 18 years or older . If the application is successful, the applicant will usually be given an initial visa for a period of 30 months if they are applying for further leave to remain from within the UK or 33 months if they are applying for entry clearance from outside of the UK.</p>\r\n<p>Upon completion of this initial period the applicant will need to apply for an extension to their visa. They must provide evidence to demonstrate the genuineness and sustainability of their marriage. If successful, they will be granted with an extension of 30 months from within the UK. Once they complete a continuous period of five years in the UK they may apply for<a href="indefinite-leave-to-remain.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;  color:#2a52a4;"> settlement </span> </a>in the UK.</p>\r\n<p>The applicant may include dependent children under the age of 18 on their application. The child may apply for .a British passport under the British Nationality Act of 1981.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Maintenance Requirement:</strong><br>\r\nApplicants applying under the new rules as off 9th July 2012 will need to provide evidence of maintenance requirement. The applicant or their settled UK partner must support the application with evidence that they can cover their living expenses without recourse to public funds for:</p>\r\n<p><em>27 months, if applying from outside the UK; or</em><br>\r\n<em> 2 years, if already in the UK and applying to switch from a different immigration category.</em></p>\r\n<p>Apart from the maintenance requirement, applicants will also need to meet other financial requirements. They must provide evidence that they have an income of at least £18,600. If they have one child dependent this amount will increase to £22,400. For any additional child dependents they will need to show availability of a further £2,400. They can meet the financial requirement by:</p>\r\n<p>income from employment or self employment of your themselves or their spouse/partner;<br>\r\ncertain income from sources other than employment, such as rent from property;<br>\r\nstate or private pensions of the applicant and/or their sponsor;<br>\r\ncash savings over a certain level</p>\r\n<h5></h5>\r\n <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a>\r\n<p><strong>Age Eligibility criteria of UK Marriage Visa (Spouse Visa)</strong><br>\r\nTo qualify for a UK Marriage Visa, a prospective applicant must meet certain mandatory conditions pertaining to age and relationship status as mentioned above.</p>\r\n<p><strong>English Language Requirements;<br>\r\n</strong>As of the 29 November 2010 applicants applying for a UK spouse visa will be required to show that they have the required level of English to successfully integrate into the UK society. The new requirements will mean that marrying or married couples will be required to show that they can speak and understand basic English. This requirement is also applicable to those applying for fiancé visas as well as those applying for a UK visa as a same-sex couple. The following may be used as evidence;</p>\r\n<p><em>they are a national of the European Economic Area and Switzerland</em><br>\r\n<em> they are a national of a majority English Speaking Country</em><br>\r\n<em> they have passed an approved English Language test</em><br>\r\n<em> they hold a bachelors degree (or equiv.) that was taught in English</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits of UK marriage Visa<br>\r\n</strong>The UK Marriage Visa or Spouse Visa allows a non-EU individual to move to the UK and live with their UK settled partner. In order to have a successful outcome of the application all the immigration rules outlined for The UK Marriage Visa must be met. Applicants must make sure that all the relevant sections of the correct UK Spouse Visa application form are filled as applications may often be rejected due to many very small mistakes or grounds.</p>\r\n<p>Once the application is approved, the applicant can stay and work in the UK without the need for applying for a UK work permit. There are no restrictions on the type of employment undertaken by a Spouse Visa holder.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other important clauses one must take into consideration for a UK marriage visa are:</strong><br>\r\nProviding false information, forged documents or if any condition remains unfulfilled, Marriage Visa applications will be rejected immediately.</p>\r\n<p>Dependents of the applicant are also permitted entry in to the UK under this visa category.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What to do next?<br>\r\n</strong>To secure a UK Spouse Visa you must make the correct application and support it with the correct evidence. In recent years many applications have been refused over very small errors made during the application. This may effect your future applications. To avoid such unnecessary situations you must speak to our highly qualified UK Immigration Consultants in the first instance. You can do so by calling us on +44 (0)207 993 4762 or by checking your eligibility by completing the free online assessment below.</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'UK Spouse Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '137-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-05 12:48:47', '2013-12-05 12:48:47', '', 137, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?p=138', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(139, 1, '2013-12-05 12:49:17', '2013-12-05 12:49:17', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                <p>\r\n				 Becoming a British citizen is the last step in the immigration process. Through naturalisation, immigrants are given the same rights as those born in the UK. If you have been granted a settlement visa, or indefinite leave to remain, applying for citizenship is the final immigration service available.<br><br>\r\nThere are several ways to apply for British citizenship. Speak to one of Global-Migrate’s immigration experts to find out the best path based on your current citizenship and visa status.\r\nTo apply for citizenship, you will need to have been living and working in the UK for three to five years. The exact amount of time will depend on your current visa category. For people living in the UK as the married spouse or civil partner of a British citizen, you will need to be resident for three years. To check the residence requirement for your case, call Global-Migrate for more information and a free assessment.<br><br>\r\nThe citizenship application includes requirements that are not found in visa applications. You will need to be of sound mind, meaning you are able to make your own decisions.<br><br>\r\nFor anyone over 10 years of age who is not stateless, you will need to demonstrate good character. This includes acting lawfully and paying taxes. Your criminal background will also be checked, and you will be asked about participation in any war crimes or genocide.<br><br>\r\nIf you are considering making an application for British citizenship, it is highly recommended that you speak to an immigration advisor first. With fifteen years of experience, Global-Migrate is a leading expert in immigration, and we can help you with your citizenship application.<br><br>\r\nWe work with hundreds of applicants every year, and our highly trained case workers keep up to date with all the changing immigration regulations. If you want to become a British citizen, get in touch with Global-Migrate today to discuss your path to naturalization.\r\n</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'British Citizenship', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'british-citizenship', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:19:51', '2014-11-14 16:19:51', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=139', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2013-12-05 12:49:17', '2013-12-05 12:49:17', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                <p>\r\n				 Becoming a British citizen is the last step in the immigration process. Through naturalisation, immigrants are given the same rights as those born in the UK. If you have been granted a settlement visa, or indefinite leave to remain, applying for citizenship is the final immigration service available.<br><br>\r\nThere are several ways to apply for British citizenship. Speak to one of Global-Migrate’s immigration experts to find out the best path based on your current citizenship and visa status.\r\nTo apply for citizenship, you will need to have been living and working in the UK for three to five years. The exact amount of time will depend on your current visa category. For people living in the UK as the married spouse or civil partner of a British citizen, you will need to be resident for three years. To check the residence requirement for your case, call Global-Migrate for more information and a free assessment.<br><br>\r\nThe citizenship application includes requirements that are not found in visa applications. You will need to be of sound mind, meaning you are able to make your own decisions.<br><br>\r\nFor anyone over 10 years of age who is not stateless, you will need to demonstrate good character. This includes acting lawfully and paying taxes. Your criminal background will also be checked, and you will be asked about participation in any war crimes or genocide.<br><br>\r\nIf you are considering making an application for British citizenship, it is highly recommended that you speak to an immigration advisor first. With fifteen years of experience, Global-Migrate is a leading expert in immigration, and we can help you with your citizenship application.<br><br>\r\nWe work with hundreds of applicants every year, and our highly trained case workers keep up to date with all the changing immigration regulations. If you want to become a British citizen, get in touch with Global-Migrate today to discuss your path to naturalization.\r\n</p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'British Citizenship', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '139-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-05 12:49:17', '2013-12-05 12:49:17', '', 139, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?p=140', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(141, 1, '2013-12-05 12:50:01', '2013-12-05 12:50:01', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p> \r\n				 </p><p>After successfully assisting thousands of applicants with their immigration queries, we have established ourselves as the most trusted and leading name in today''s UK immigration industry. We are proud to have clients who are happy with our high quality services. As We have a proven track record of thousands of successful visa applications and happy clients, our existing or previous client''s are always referring their friends or family to us, thus making us believe we deliver what we promise. Our team of highly experienced, expert immigration consultants are familiar with today''s forever changing immigration regulations. We are proud to provide free assessment to all candidates who contact us. Complete our free assessment now which is quick and simple and let us take the stress on your behalf.</p>\r\n<p>We offer a wide range of UK visa and uk immigration assistance to anyone wishing to lodge a strong application to the UK Home Office (UK Border Agency) &amp; British Embassies all over the world. Our highly experienced teams of OISC registered caseworkers are assist clients with all kinds of UK immigration applications. Whether your case is a straightforward immigration application or you would like to re-apply due to an unfair Home Office/UK Embassy decision or an error in your previous application we are here to help.</p>\r\n<p>The UK immigration process can be difficult as there are many different UK visas to choose from. They all have different rules and regulations that one has to meet. Therefore to avoid rejection of their applications thousands of people use our expert help and advice which becomes useful for them in the end. With the help of our professional and highly qualified UK immigration legal case workers, you can rest assured that your application is in good hands.</p>\r\n<p>Why don’t you try our free assessment tool to determine which Visa is suitable for you, or alternatively you can call us on +44 (0) 207 9934762 to discuss your case in depth.</p>\r\n<p>Contact us now for all your UK Visa inquiries now.</p>\r\n<p>We can assist you with any of the following applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Family Visas</h4>\r\n<p>We have a dedicated team of UK immigration caseworker''s ready to help you with your UK visa services whether that be through your relationship, or ancestry. You could be looking to apply for a Fiancé visas, Marriage/spouse visas, De facto/unmarried partner visas, Same-sex/civil partner visas, Family dependant visas, or, like mentioned before a UK Ancestry visas.</p>\r\n<p><a href="uk-spouse-visa.html"><strong>Spouse Visas</strong></a> - If you are a settled UK citizen, a Spouse or Marriage visa allows your husband or wife to join you in the UK. Our Spouse visa application team can help you in obtaining this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="defacto-visa.html"><strong>Unmarried Partner Visas</strong></a> - This application for anyone who has lived with their (unmarried) UK settled partner for at least two years. Our dedicated case worker can help you apply for a UK Unmarried Partner visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="defacto-visa.html"><strong>Civil Partner Visas</strong></a> - The Civil Partner visa''s eligibility criteria is very similar to a UK Spouse visa, however, it applies only to those who are in a same-sex relation with a UK settled resident or a British/EU citizen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="fiance-visa.html"><strong>Fiancé Visas</strong></a> - You may apply for this visa if you are engaged to a UK settled person. Although it sounds like a "Do it yourself" application, the fact is that the refusal rate of all application made by the applicant themselves is very high. This is merely due to the fact that this requires a lot of documents which our legal team can help you prepare. This is the first step to enter the UK to live with your UK settled partner and gradually apply for a UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="uk-ancestry-visas.html"><strong>UK Ancestry Visas</strong></a> - If you have British ancestors, UK Ancestry Visas are a UK visa immigration option. We can help you with this application whether you are in the UK or outside the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>UK Family Dependant Visas</strong> - This visa is for individuals who want their dependants to join them in the UK. We specialise in all UK Family dependency visa advice, and services.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p><a href="indefinite-leave-to-remain.html"><strong>Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR)</strong></a><br>\r\nIndefinite Leave to Remain, Permanent Residency, or Settlement assistance (UK ILR) is the final application before you can apply for British Citizenship. Our UK immigration caseworkers can help you apply for a UK ILR via a postal application or a same day premium service.</p>\r\n<p><a href="british-citizenship.html"><strong>Naturalisation</strong></a><br>\r\nNaturalisation is the last application you would make to become a British citizen. We help most of our client''s who have used us for their UK visa and than their UK ILR to apply for British Citizenship through naturalisation.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p><strong>UK Work Permit and UK working visas</strong><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate provide assistance with a complete range of UK employment visas including Tier 1 General Highly Skilled visas: which replaced the HSMP, and Tier 2 visas: that replaced the UK Work Permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-1-general-visa-extension.html"><strong>Tier 1 General Visas</strong></a> - Points Based System (PBS) visa replaced the previously popular HSMP. A fresh application for this visa is no longer available anymore. However, we can help you to extend this visa via a postal application or a same day premium service. You may also apply for your ILR if you have completed your required time in the UK on a Tier 1 General Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-1-exceptional-talent-visa.html"><strong>Tier 1 Exceptional Talent Visas</strong></a> - For non-European Economic Area nationals who are internationally recognised as the world-leading talent in science and the arts, Tier 1 Exceptional Talent visas provide a route for entry to the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-2-visa.html"><strong>Tier 2 General Visas</strong></a> - Tier 2 General Points based application is designed for skilled workers with a job offer, from a sponsored UK company. This replaced the UK Work Permit system and is only issued to UK-based employers employing foreign workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-2-visa.html"><strong>Tier 2 Intra-Company Transfer </strong></a>- Intra-Company Transfer visas are for individuals who are transferring from overseas to a post in the UK within the same company to which they are currently employed with.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-2-visa.html"><strong>Tier 2 Sportsperson Visas</strong></a> - Elite sportspersons and coaches must apply for a Tier 2 Sportsperson visa when seeking entry into the UK to take part in a sport activity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-2-visa.html"><strong>Tier 2 Minister of Religion Visas</strong></a> - It may be necessary to apply for a Tier 2 Minister of Religion visa for those offered a job as a minister of a religion within the UK by an employer holding a valid Tier 2 sponsorship license.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-2-sponsorship-licence.html"><strong>Tier 2 Sponsor License</strong></a> - To employ workers from outside of the European Economic Area, employers must obtain a Tier 2 Sponsor License. There are various restrictions and limitations on this application there we strongly advise you to get in touch with our UK Tier 2 specialist team at your earliest convenience.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-1-entrepreneur-visa.html"><strong>Tier 1 Entrepreneur Visas</strong></a> - The Tier 1 Entrepreneur visa is UK points based visa, for individuals either starting a new business or with intentions in acquiring an existing business. The applicant must show evidence of the required funds and support their application with various other documents. To get a successful outcome of this application it is a must that you seek legal advice and assistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-1-entrepreneur-visa.html"><strong>Tier 1 Graduate Entrepreneur</strong></a> - This type of visa is for graduates who have world class of innovative ideas or entrepreneurial skills and have been identified by UK higher education institutions. They can extend their stay to the UK after graduation to establish their business.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a href="tier-1-investor-visa.html"><strong>Tier 1 Investor Visas</strong></a> - The UK Tier 1 Investor Visa is a points-based visa allowing a foreign national to immigrate to the UK to invest large amounts of capital in a business, bonds or even property. We provide a bespoke service for this visa for high net-worth individuals from assistance with their investment via a venture capital, property search to a name a few from the entire relocation service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>UK Business Visitor Visas</strong> - The UK Business Visitor Visa can be issued to a business visitor for a temporary visit, and depending on the frequency of travel required, it can be issued anywhere from six months to five years.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Immigration to the UK for European Nationals</strong><br>\r\nUnder the current legislation European Economic Area (EEA) includes thirty countries; however, nationals of the previous EEA and Switzerland are still able to work in the UK without restriction. Individuals who are EU nationals exercising treaty rights in the UK may be able to bring their family to the UK to live and settle with them. Applicants who are married to, or in a civil partnership with an EU citizen are eligible to apply for an EEA Family Permit. Unmarried partners, fiancés, and fiancées can also apply for UK immigration through various different routes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="eea-residents-permit.html"><strong>EEA Family Permit</strong></a> - An EEA Family Permit is a legal route of ‘entry clearance’ into the UK for a non-EEA family members of an EEA national.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="eea-residents-permit.html"><strong>EEA Permanent Residence</strong></a> - EEA Permanent Residence confirms the right of permanent residence in the UK for EEA nationals and their non-EEA family members and may be valid for up to 5 years. Finally the applicant can apply for permanent residence by becoming a British Citizen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="eea-residents-permit.html"><strong>Work Permits for Bulgarians and Romanians</strong></a> - Romanians &amp; Bulgarians wanting to work in the UK are required to apply for a work permit. We can give you advice on how to do so. Please contact us now if you require help</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tier-4-student-visa.html"><strong>Tier 4 Student Visas</strong></a> - Tier 4 General student visas are for overseas students who wish to study in the UK, and have received an offer of study from a Tier 4 recognised UK educational institute. All students who are already in the UK on a Tier 4 General Visa may also apply for extension if they wish to pursue their studies in the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tier 4 Sponsor License</strong> &ndash; This application is for all the education providers who wish to teach international students. We specialize in such applications and can help you apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other UK Immigration options</strong><br>\r\n<strong><br>\r\n</strong><a href="tier-5-working-visa.html"><strong>Tier 5 Youth Mobility Scheme Visas</strong></a> - The Youth Mobility Scheme was designed to enable foreign nationals of specific countries and age groups to gain entry clearance to live and work in the UK for a limited period of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="tourist-visa.html"><strong>UK Tourist/ Visitor Visas</strong></a> &ndash; All applicants who wish to travel to the United Kingdom (UK) as a visitor to visit family members, or come for a holiday as a tourist &amp; short term visits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To find out more about any of the above visa categories please use our FREE assessment tool to find out if you are eligible for the visa that you require or call us on +44 (0)207 9934762</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left"><a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n</td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'UK Immigration Visa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'uk-immigration-visa', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:53', '2014-11-14 16:20:53', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=141', 0, 'page', '', 0);
