ded they meet the requirements for <a href="british-citizenship.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#274789;">British citizenship</span></a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong><br><br>\r\nThe applicant must have a settled status in Britain. This usually means that the candidate must have been resident in Great Britain on the same visa class for at least four years. The only exception to this is for people on marriage visas or De Facto visas, who only require two years and for periods of exceptionally long-term residency (10 years legal, or 14 years as a combination of illegal and legal residency).</p>\r\n<p>Ancestry and being an EU National can be a way in, as can marriage. All applicants have to demonstrate sufficient understanding of the English language and the English way of life in order to qualify.</p>\r\n<p>Global-Migrate can make an application for you Indefinite Leave to Remain (Also known as the ILR) using one of our premium services, which means that you will have your passport back within 24 hours. Certain categories cannot be applied for using the premium services, for e.g. ILR through <a href="long-term-residency-visa.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#274789;">long residency</span></a> (10 years legal stay in the UK), partner of an EEA national or an EEA national who has spent 5 years in the UK</p>\r\n<p>The UKBA might not make a decision within 24 hours in some cases even if you opt for the premium service. This will depend on the individuals application.</p>\r\n<p>An application for ILR can only be made 28 days prior to you becoming eligible for the application.</p>\r\n<p>Do you think you qualify for your ILR? To find out more please call us directly on +44 (0)207 9934762 or use our FREE assessment form.</p> <p></p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'UK ILR', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '151-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-05 12:53:34', '2013-12-05 12:53:34', '', 151, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?p=152', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(153, 1, '2013-12-05 12:54:05', '2013-12-05 12:54:05', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="normalTxt" colspan="2" valign="top">The United Kingdom offers a special type of visa for people from outside the European Economic Area (EEA) who want to immigrate for work. These visas, which took the place of work permits, are part of the Points-Based System and are called Tier 2 Visas.\r\n\r\n\r\nAll types of Tier 2 visas are assessed using the points-based system. You will be given points for things like your ability to speak English, your salary, and your maintenance funds. To find out whether you have enough points to be approved, get in touch with Global Migrate.\r\n\r\n\r\nTo get a Tier 2 visa, you’ll also need to have been offered a job by a legitimate sponsor in the United Kingdom. Within the Tier 2 category, there are several types of visa based on the type of employment.\r\n<a class="more" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> </a>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTier 2 (General) covers most types of job. It requires that the job is a gap in the market that a settled person cannot fill. Depending on salary, there are limits as to how many people can be granted this type of visa in a year. Global Migrate can help you determine if you will be able to get this type of Tier 2 visa, so call our advisors today.\r\n\r\n\r\nTier 2 (Sportsperson) is limited to sports players and coaches at the highest levels.\r\n\r\n\r\nTier 2 (Intra company transfer) is for people who are employees of a multinational companies and are being transferred to their company’s UK offices.\r\n\r\n\r\nTier 2 (Minister of religion) visas are for ministers and missionaries coming to the UK to specifically work within a religious order. The UK Border Agency lays out specific roles that can be filled by somebody on this type of visa. For the most up-to-date information, get in touch with Global Migrate’s advisors, who can assess whether you qualify for this type of visa.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left"><a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php">\r\n<div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n<td align="right">\r\n<table width="157" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="10"></td>\r\n<td width="20"></td>\r\n<td width="36"></td>\r\n<td width="34"></td>\r\n<td width="41"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Tier 2 Visa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tier-2-visa', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:39', '2014-11-14 16:20:39', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=153', 0, 'page', '', 0),
