\nGet in touch with Global-Migrate today for a free initial assessment. Our advisors can help you determine if you will qualify for a Tier 1 (Investor) visa.<br><br>\r\n\r\n</p></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'Tier -1 Investor Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '173-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-05 13:02:28', '2013-12-05 13:02:28', '', 173, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?p=174', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(175, 1, '2013-12-05 13:05:59', '2013-12-05 13:05:59', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p></p><h4>There are various different categories under the Tier 2 visa application route for the UK</h4><p></p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Tier 2 General Work Permits</h4>\r\nThe Tier 2 work permit is designed for highly skilled workers who are from outside of the EEU &ndash; the European Economic Area. The permit grants them a UK visa on the basis that they have a job offer and meet a number of skill requirements.<p></p>\r\n<p>At Global-Migrate we provide a tailor made service designed to assist these highly skilled individuals to get a successful outcome of their visa.</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Benefits of a Tier 2 visa</h4>\r\nTier 2 immigration is a UK visa which offers a possibility of permanent residency in the UK to highly skilled foreign nationals. It allows large organisations to transfer the skills of new and existing staff members from outside the UK into this country.<p></p>\r\n<p>The Tier 2 work permit visas can last between one day and five years, depending on the time frame specified by the sponsoring company. Although the Tier 2 permit is not a permanent residency visa, those who do live and work in the UK for a minimum of five years on this permit may apply for Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR) in the UK. Once they have completed a year on the ILR category they may be eligible for British Citizenship through the Naturalisation route</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>What criteria do you need to meet?</h4>\r\nThis application is a point’s based visa. Tier 2 visa applicants are assessed based on potential Earnings, English language skills and available funds to support their stay in the UK.<p></p>\r\n<p>It is the employer’s responsibility to make sure that a candidate is eligible and suitable. Immigration compliance checks can be carried out and require no notice. Employers will be awarded a sponsorship license, according to the UK Border Agency’s risk assessment. Pay must be fair and equal to what a UK national would earn in that role, and the role must be above NVQ level 3. Applications for spouse and dependents may be made in conjunction with a Tier 2 permit due to the potential settlement that could follow such a visa. For more information please use the FREE online assessment tool and receive expert professional help.</p>\r\n  <a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"></a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Tier 2 Change of Employment</h4>\r\nTier 2 immigration candidates are sponsored by an employer as part of gaining their permit to work in the UK as a highly skilled worker. However, candidates can change their employment whilst in the UK, but they must obtain a Certificate of Sponsorship once again and they must be reassessed against the points test.<p></p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Duration</h4>\r\nThe change of employer requires a new sponsorship, therefore it is classified as a new permit and means you can work for a period of one to five years all over again, depending on the sponsor’s contract offer duration.<p></p>\r\n<p>The duration is also at the discretion of the Home Office and these changes are temporary immigration services, not a route to settlement. Settlement can be pursued after five years, though. Due to the temporary nature, you do not have the freedom to work in the UK aside this agreed role.</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>What criteria do you need to meet?</h4>\r\nThe position for which the change of employment working visa is being sought must meet National Vocation Qualification (NVQ) level 3 or above, as the original application for a Tier 2 permit did. If the candidate in question works in a specific profession, they may be required to register with the relevant governing body.<p></p>\r\n<p>A candidate applying for a permit to work in the UK must possess a relevant degree or a non-relevant degree plus a year’s experience. The same can apply to a HND level qualification and again, if irrelevant then there must be a year’s relevant work experience alongside it. A candidate can be eligible with no degree if they have three years of relevant experience.</p>\r\n<p>If a position is listed on the UK shortage list then the employer does not need to advertise the vacancy before sponsoring an applicant. They must prove an attempt to recruit from within the UK and EU workforce.</p>\r\n<p>Global-Migrate can help make sure that your company abides by all the relevant rules and regulations in applying for a Tier 2 permit. With our experienced staff and their prior knowledge of immigration and employment law, we can make this process as smooth as possible, all by using our FREE online assessment tool.</p>\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"></a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Tier 2 Intra Company Transfer</h4>\r\nIntra-Company Transfers (ICTs) allow multi-national employers to transfer overseas employees to fill a specific position which they have been unable to fill from the local resident workforce. The Tier 2 permit in general allows non-citizens to work in the UK for a specific time period and role, as agreed by an employer. The company must prove that the employee is appropriately skilled, though.<p></p>\r\n<p>With Global-Migrate you can quickly discover what rules and regulations you need to be aware of and how to get the easiest application route sorted. Click the FREE online assessment tool below for more.</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Benefits</h4>\r\nThe main benefit of this type of UK immigration service is that an employer does not need to demonstrate that the position has been advertised before applying for an ICT. No points-based assessment is required either, however you will have to explain why the transfer is necessary and detail its duration.<p></p>\r\n<p>Like all Tier 2 permits, the application can last from a day to five years, depending on the sponsor company’s request, but is not intended as a route to settlement and at the expiry of the permit candidates will be expected to return to their former country.</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>What criteria do you need to meet?</h4>\r\nTo be eligible for the ICT visa service the position must warrant an NVQ level 3 or above, and the person must meet that criteria. Furthermore, if the candidate is a member of a specific profession they may be required to be registered with the appropriate governing body. In addition, a selected candidate must have a level of knowledge that is essential and relevant to the post.<p></p>\r\n<p>The employee for whom the ICT is being sought must have been employed by the overseas company for a period of six months or more prior to the application. Documentary evidence of this relationship must be produced before visas of this class can be issued.</p>\r\n<p>Partners and dependents can come over as well, and their length of stay will be in line with that of the permit length. For more assistance please use our FREE online assessment tool. Expert advisors at Global-Migrate are on hand to assist and support all immigration applications.</p>\r\n<a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"></a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Tier 2 Minister of Religion application</h4>\r\nThe tier 2 Minister of Religion category is designed for candidates who are coming to the UK to perform pastoral duties for their religious center. The applicant may come to the UK in the capacity of a monk, nun, priest or a member of similar religious community. This will entitle the candidate to stay in the country for a maximum of 3 years. The employer must possess a Tier 2 sponsorship license.<p></p>\r\n<p>With Global-Migrate you can quickly discover what rules and regulations you need to be aware of and how to get the your application or a Tier 2 Minister of Religion initiated. Check your visa eligibility online by taking our online assessment.</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>Benefits</h4>\r\nThe main benefit of this visa is that the applicant will be allowed to work on a fulltime basis under this scheme for their sponsor.<p></p>\r\n<p>This visa is issued initially for a period of 3 years, which can be further extended. Upon successful completion of a total of 5 years, the applicant may apply for Indefinite Leave to Remain in the UK. Permanent resident status holders can even go on to sponsor their non-British dependents to come to the UK and become eligible to apply for naturalisation and UK citizenship.</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>What criteria do you need to meet?</h4>\r\nTo be eligible for this application the major requirement of is to score a minimum of 70 points in the sponsorship, maintenance and English language categories. Candidates applying as a Minister of Religion must carry out duties which can include but not limited to;<p></p>\r\n<p>Acting as a leader of a religious ceremony<br>\r\nEducation, preaching and teaching religion<br>\r\nPerforming rituals of marriages, funerals and other religious activities<br>\r\nCounselling or providing welfare support to members of a congregation<br>\r\nConducting missionary activities<br>\r\nMonitoring and coordinating the work of local preachers and volunteers</p>\r\n<p></p><h4>What to do next?</h4>\r\nIf you would like to get help or advice with any of the above application please call our UK team on +44 (0)2079934762 for a free impartial advice.<p></p></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'Tier 2 - General  Visa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tier-2-general-visa', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:39', '2014-11-14 16:20:39', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=175', 0, 'page', '', 0);
