(193, 1, '2013-12-05 13:13:15', '2013-12-05 13:13:15', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n               \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p> \r\n				Long-term residents of the United Kingdom may be able to apply for settlement based on this residency. This settlement path, called long residence, granted indefinite leave to remain to migrants who had resided in the UK continuously for 10 or 14 years, depending on the specific circumstances.<br><br>\r\nBecause of changing immigration rules, it is important to speak to a qualified immigration advisor before applying for a long-term residency settlement. Global-Migrate’s advisors are trained and can help you prepare an application based on the current rules.<br><br>\r\nBefore 9 July 2012, long residence was granted after 14 years of continuous residence. If an application was made before that date, it will still be considered under the previous rules.<br><br>\r\nApplications made after 9 July 2012, however, are judged by the new rules. Call Global-Migrate to find out what rules will be used to judge your application, and to get an assessment of your case.<br><br>\r\nThe current immigration rules will allow settlement after 10 years of continuous lawful residence. This means that you will have to have been in the UK for that period of time, and that you did not breach the terms of your visa at any point. You must also meet language and life requirements, as you would for any settlement visa.<br><br>\r\nIf you have been in the UK for 10 years, there is no limit as to when you can apply for settlement. After 10 years you become eligible, and remain eligible. However, your case will be judged by the rules in effect at the time of your application. If you wait to apply, the rules are subject to change.<br><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate helps hundreds of people every year who want to apply for settlement in the United Kingdom. Our team of experienced advisors can help you figure out if your application will be successful. If we believe your application will be successful, we can help you through the entire application process.<br><br>\r\nTo find out more about long term residency, and the current requirements, get in touch with us today.\r\n</p></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'Long Term Residency', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'long-term-residency', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:24', '2014-11-14 16:20:24', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=193', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(194, 1, '2013-12-05 13:13:15', '2013-12-05 13:13:15', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n               \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p> \r\n				Long-term residents of the United Kingdom may be able to apply for settlement based on this residency. This settlement path, called long residence, granted indefinite leave to remain to migrants who had resided in the UK continuously for 10 or 14 years, depending on the specific circumstances.<br><br>\r\nBecause of changing immigration rules, it is important to speak to a qualified immigration advisor before applying for a long-term residency settlement. Global-Migrate’s advisors are trained and can help you prepare an application based on the current rules.<br><br>\r\nBefore 9 July 2012, long residence was granted after 14 years of continuous residence. If an application was made before that date, it will still be considered under the previous rules.<br><br>\r\nApplications made after 9 July 2012, however, are judged by the new rules. Call Global-Migrate to find out what rules will be used to judge your application, and to get an assessment of your case.<br><br>\r\nThe current immigration rules will allow settlement after 10 years of continuous lawful residence. This means that you will have to have been in the UK for that period of time, and that you did not breach the terms of your visa at any point. You must also meet language and life requirements, as you would for any settlement visa.<br><br>\r\nIf you have been in the UK for 10 years, there is no limit as to when you can apply for settlement. After 10 years you become eligible, and remain eligible. However, your case will be judged by the rules in effect at the time of your application. If you wait to apply, the rules are subject to change.<br><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate helps hundreds of people every year who want to apply for settlement in the United Kingdom. Our team of experienced advisors can help you figure out if your application will be successful. If we believe your application will be successful, we can help you through the entire application process.<br><br>\r\nTo find out more about long term residency, and the current requirements, get in touch with us today.\r\n</p></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'Long Term Residency', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-05 13:13:15', '2013-12-05 13:13:15', '', 193, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?p=194', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(195, 1, '2013-12-05 13:14:44', '2013-12-05 13:14:44', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p>\r\n				  Anyone with the Right of Abode has no restrictions to live and work in the UK. They can enter and leave the UK without any immigration restrictions.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAll British citizens have the right of abode in the United Kingdom.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSome Commonwealth citizens also have the right of abode.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIf you wish to claim the right of abode, you must prove it by producing:\r\n</p><ul>\r\n<li>a United Kingdom passport describing you as a British citizen or a British subject with the right of abode</li>\r\n<li>a United Kingdom identity card describing you as a British citizen or a British subject with the right of abode</li>\r\n<li>a certificate of entitlement to the right of abode in the United Kingdom that has been issued by the Government of the United Kingdom or on its behalf.\r\n</li></ul>\r\nIf you are not a British Citizen that’s ok. You may still have the Right of Abode if, on 31 December 1982, you were:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>a Commonwealth citizen with a parent who, at the time of your birth or legal adoption, was a citizen of the United Kingdom and Colonies because he/she was born in the United Kingdom</li>\r\n<li>a female Commonwealth citizen who was, or had been, married to a man who had the right of abode. You must have been married to him before 1 January 1983.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNational’s of certain countries do not have the Right of Abode as there countries left the Commonwealth before 1983 and joined it again afterwards. South Africa and Pakistan are an example of such countries.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSuch applications can be complex and may require professional assistance as it may not be easy to convince the UK government that you genuinely have the Right of Abode. These applications require a lot of documents as well and need to be submitted in the right order.\r\n<br><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate is a leading UK immigration consultancy. We help hundreds of client’s every year who are interested in UK citizenship, a work visa and even a temporary visa. Global-Migrate’s consulants will guide you to the best UK visa which meets your requirement.\r\n<br><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate has fully qualified and trained UK visas specialists. This allows us to provide our client’s with a service second to none. Our rate of success continues to grow every day and with our help you could soon be lodging a strong application. To enquire about how to become a British Citizen why don’t you use our Free assessment tool. <p></p></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"> </a>\r\n</td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'UK Right of Abode', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'uk-right-of-abode', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:53', '2014-11-14 16:20:53', '', 0, 'http://creativewebdesignlondon.com/global-migrat/?page_id=195', 0, 'page', '', 0),
