(283, 1, '2014-03-07 07:29:16', '2014-03-07 07:29:16', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                 \r\nIf you’re the family member of an Australian citizen or permanent resident, you can join them in Australia on a family visa. Family members of eligible New Zealand citizens can also migrate to Australia on one of these popular visas.<br><br>\r\nYour relationship will determine which visa is right for you. If you’re not sure which visa you should apply for, get in touch with us today for your free visa assessment with Global-Migrate’s trained immigration advisors. We are the UK’s largest and most trusted Australian immigration consultancies, and can help you determine your immigration options.\r\n</p><h4>Partner (Spouse) Visas</h4>\r\nFor Australian immigration, partners include fiancés, married partners, and de facto partners, including those in same-sex relationship. A partner visa will allow you to enter and/or gain permanent residency in Australia. To find out if you are eligible for this type of visa, call our MARA certified consultants.\r\n<h4>Parent Visas</h4>\r\nIf you are the parent of an Australian citizen or permanent resident, or eligible New Zealand citizen, you can apply for a parent visa. This type of visa can give you permanent residency in Australia. If you want more details about how you or your parents can migrate to Australia, get in touch with us today to discuss visa options.\r\n\r\n<h4>Child Visas</h4>\r\nChildren of Australian citizens and permanent residents, and eligible New Zealand citizens, can also travel to and reside permanently in Australia. Child visas are available for dependent children, orphan relatives, and adopted children. Our visa advisors can help you apply for this type of visa, so get in touch today.<br><br>\r\nOther family visas are also available, including visas for aged dependent relatives, carers, and remaining relatives. If you are considering making a family visa application, speak to our trained and qualified advisors for up-to-date information, and a free visa assessment.<br><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate’s immigration consultants are MARA certified, and can help you determine the right visa for your individual case.\r\n\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n   ', 'Australia Family Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '57-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:29:16', '2014-03-07 07:29:16', '', 57, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/57-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(284, 1, '2014-03-07 07:30:06', '2014-03-07 07:30:06', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  <span style="font-size:16px; font-family:''Trebuchet MS''; color:blue;">Thinking of moving to Australia? Don’t think, do it, as this would be one of the best decisions you would ever make …</span><br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n                  Well if you have, then Global-Migrate is here to assist. As migration agents we completely understand that migration to Australia is not just a lengthy process but also complicated. However, with many years or practice and experience we fully understand the standard of work required in your application process for a successful application. It’s not just about complying with all the regulations, it’s as much about presenting the facts of your case in the right way to ensure that your application gets through the system the first time you apply. As a company that hires MARA registered agents we are bound by a strict code of conduct for your protection <a style="color:blue" href="https://www.mara.gov.au/Code-of-Conduct/Code-of-Conduct/default.aspx">(MARA Code of Conduct)</a><br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n                  Covering a total area of 7.69 million square kilometers, mainland Australia is the world’s largest island &ndash; but smallest continent.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAustralia is also the only continent that is governed as a single country. It is sometimes informally referred to as an ‘island’ continent, surrounded by oceans.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nMost Australians are immigrants or the descendants of immigrants who arrived during the past two hundred years from more than 200 countries. The most commonly spoken language in Australia is English, and the most commonly practiced religion is Christianity, although foreign languages and other religions are also common.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAustralian Immigration can be quite a complex and a time consuming process, therefore, we strongly advise you to seek assistance from people in the know how. A regulated consultancy who hires a MARA agent like us is definitely a good option. This reduces the chance of a rejection in your visa application and most definitely is a wise decision if you are deciding to make a life changing decision for a better future for you and your family.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nYou may apply for immigration to Australia via many different routes. You can be a skilled worker whose occupation might be in demand or you might be a school or college leaver who wants to migrate to Australia and get work experience.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nGlobal-Migrate specialises in all Australian Skilled Migration, Work Permits, Study Visas and Working Holiday Visas for Australia. We hire a team of MARA regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian Government to give advice and assist someone like you.<br>\r\n </p><div class="more2"><a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div> </a> </div><br>\r\nThe most common and popular immigration routes for Australia are;\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="australia-partner-visa-australia-marriage-visa.html">Partner Visas</a></h3>\r\nThere are many different types of partner visa to Australia. These include the Spouse Partner Visa, the Defacto Partner Visa, the Interdependent Partner Visa and the Prospective Marriage Partner Visa.<p></p>\r\n<p></p><h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="australian-family-visa.html">Family Visas</a></h3>\r\nFamily Migration is one of the most common and popular way of entering Australia legally. There are a number of different types of applications you can apply for under this category. You may qualify if you have a family member who is a citizen of Australia. This could be your parents or your children or even a partner who you would like to go and settle with. Whatever the situation, if you have a family member who is a citizen or a permanent resident of Australia, we can help. So why don''t you call our specialist Australian immigration team now on +44 (0)2079934762<p></p>\r\n<p></p><h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-189.html">Skilled Independent Visa - (Subclass 189)</a></h3>\r\nThe Skilled Independent visa is a points-based application. To qualify for the independant visa, you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements, you will be eligible for this visa. This visa is without a doubt the most desired route of immigration to Australia, however, you need to score very high points to be able to apply for this visa. This is an independent application which means no state, or territory will sponsor you and you need to score the required points without having to claim any bonus points for sponsorship. Although the application takes between 12 - 16 months, but once approved you are a permanent resident in Australia and you have the flexibility to settle anywhere in Australia. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian Skilled independent immigration process. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.<p></p>\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-190.html">Skilled Nominated Visa &ndash; (Subclass 190)</a></h3>\r\nThe Skilled Sponsored visa is a points-based application. To qualify for this type of visa you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements you may be eligible for this visa. Once approved you become a permanent resident of Australia from day one however you have a restriction to your stay in Australia, where you need to live in the region that sponsors your occupation for at least 24 months. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian sponsored immigration. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-489.html">Skilled Nominated or Sponsored Visa &ndash; (Subclass 489)</a></h3>\r\nThe Skilled Regional Sponsored visa is initially based on meeting a point score. To qualify for this visa, you must first pass basic requirements. You get points for your age, English competence, training, work experience and having an eligible relative (or a state) able to sponsor you. Once you meet these requirements, you may be eligible for this type of visa. This is initially a 3 year visa sponsored by a state. You may apply for permanent residency after 2 years if you meet the criteria. For this application your occupation MUST be nominated by a state. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian state sponsored immigration. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="australia-work-holiday-visa.html">Working Holiday Visa</a></h3>\r\nThis visa is for people aged 18 to 30 years of age, who are interested in a working holiday of up to 12 months in Australia. You can extend this visa automatically after the 12 months by another 1 year.\r\n\r\nIf you are granted this visa you can, enter Australia within 12 months of grant, leave and re-enter Australia any number of times while the visa is valid and study for up to four months if you wish\r\n\r\nTo get more information on any of the above visa either call us on +44 (0)207 9934762 or click on the desired visa option on the left.\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n    ', 'Australia Immigration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:30:06', '2014-03-07 07:30:06', '', 77, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/77-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(285, 1, '2014-03-07 07:30:47', '2014-03-07 07:30:47', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n               The Partner Visa is a way for people married to Australian citizens and permanent residents, as well as eligible New Zealand citizens, to live in Australia. When you are granted a partner visa, you will be able to live, work, and study in Australia.<br><br>\r\nIf you are considering applying for a partner visa, call Global-migrate for a free visa assessment. We have a 100% success rate for partner visa applications, and can offer advice on your application. Our advisors are highly trained immigration professionals. We also offer a ‘no visa, no fee’ policy, and guarantee that we can help our clients submit a strong application.<br><br>\r\nFor a partner visa, you will need to provide evidence of your relationship. This needs to be show in a variety of ways, and many people who apply without the assistance of an immigration professional fail to show sufficient evidence. We can help you figure out what you need to include, and can help you as you write your personal history statement.<br><br>\r\nYou will also need to meet certain character and legal requirements. These are fairly straightforward, but can get confusing. If you have any questions about what else might be required of you for this type of visa, Global-Migrate can help.<br><br>\r\nWhen you are granted your partner visa, you will generally be given a temporary visa while a decision is made on your permanent visa. Your permanent visa will allow you to live, work, and study in Australia permanently. It will also allow you to earn certain benefits, and will allow you to apply for Australian citizenship after you have met certain criteria.<br><br>\r\nIf you are planning on moving to Australia with your partner, Global-Migrate’s advisors can help answer any questions you might have. Give us a call today to get a free visa assessment.\r\n\r\n                  </p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n', 'Australia Partner or "Spouse" Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '55-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:30:47', '2014-03-07 07:30:47', '', 55, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/55-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(286, 1, '2014-03-07 07:31:27', '2014-03-07 07:31:27', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  Welcome to Global-Migrate, UK’s most trusted Australian Visa and Immigration consultancy. Our MARA regulated agent’s have a track record of successfully securing marriage or spouse visas for you and your spouse.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<a style="color:#003399" href="australia-visa-and-immigration.html">Australian immigration </a>under the spouse visa or marriage visa category is for applicants who are married to either a “Settled” Australian citizen, permanent resident or an eligible New Zealand citizen. At Global-Migrate we hire a dedicated team of regulated consultants to advise those who might be interested in migrating to Australia with their Australian Spouse or Partners. You could already be present in Australia and thinking of switching over to a this visa category or you might want to apply for this visa from the UK or any other part of the world, our specialist team can help you secure your visa.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nWith a 100% success rate with marriage visa applications and a No Visa No Fee policy we are sure to provide you with a service second to none.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nA partner visa application is closely scrutinised by the Department of Immigration and Citizenship. Success in the application is dependent on the quality of evidence of the relationship, hence why most of the applicants who contact us end up using our service as we guarantee them a strong submission of their application.\r\n\r\n</p><h4>Evidence of relationship</h4>\r\nThe couple applying for the partner visa need to provide documentation that demonstrates (for the 12 months prior to the date of lodging that they have a mutual commitment to a shared life together.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nEvidence of this shared life needs to be shown over a range of areas, from financial commitment to nature of the household to the social context of the relationship. Each partner must write a personal history statement that outlines their development and future intentions of the relationship. Many applicants fail due to showing insufficient or contradictory information.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nYou may apply for this visa if you are a Spouse or a Common-Law partner of an Australian Citizen.\r\n\r\n<h4>Duration</h4>\r\n\r\nA spouse partner visa or a defacto partner visa may initially be temporary, or permanent from the day of granting. The length of the relationship and children influences the partner visa subclass that applies. If the partner visa is initially temporary, the couple must show their ongoing relationship over the first two years to apply for a residency partner visa.\r\n\r\n<h4>How to apply?</h4>\r\n\r\nThe main applicant must be sponsored by an Australian citizen, permanent resident, or eligible New Zealand citizen. They must be able to provide evidence that they are legally married to the sponsor and in a ‘genuine, continuous relationship’ with them which they intend to continue after arrival in Australia.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nTo start your visa process you can contact us and speak to our highly qualified consultant’s for a no obligation free visa assessment\r\n\r\n<h4>Benefit of a Partner Visa?</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce granted, the applicant will have no restriction to work and reside in Australia.\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n    ', 'Australia Spouse Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '79-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:31:27', '2014-03-07 07:31:27', '', 79, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/79-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(478, 1, '2014-03-28 11:09:37', '2014-03-28 11:09:37', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="normalTxt" colspan="2" valign="top">Australian Visa under the Study Visa category is for applicants who plan to go to Australia for higher education. At Global-Migrate we hire a dedicated team of MARA regulated consultants to advise those who might be interested in migrating to Australia to study. As we have been in business for over 15 years and work with all established education institutions in Australia we are in a position to help you secure a place at the University, School or College of your choice.\r\n\r\nAustralia has a reputation for having some of the world’s leading education institutions. By Joining the thousands of satisfied international students studying in Australia, you will experience a unique kind of education.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost you will need to be enrolled by a recognized university in Australia, which we can help you with. Once you have an acceptance letter you would be able to make an application for a study visa provided you have enough finances to cover your tuition fee and your cost of living for the entire period of your stay.\r\n\r\nWe also provide a complete relocation service from Airport transfers to finding an accommodation and opening bank accounts to name a few\r\n\r\nYour student visa will list the conditions that apply specifically to you. It is important to comply with your visa conditions to avoid visa cancellation.\r\n\r\nThere many different types of study visas available.\r\n<h4>How to apply</h4>\r\nTo find out more please contact our Australian team on +44 (0)207 9934762 or use our free assessment tool below</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left"></td>\r\n<td align="right">\r\n<table width="157" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="10"></td>\r\n<td width="20"></td>\r\n<td width="36"></td>\r\n<td width="34"></td>\r\n<td width="41"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Australia Study Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '59-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-28 11:09:37', '2014-03-28 11:09:37', '', 59, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/59-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(287, 1, '2014-03-07 07:31:58', '2014-03-07 07:31:58', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  Australian Visa under the Study Visa category is for applicants who plan to go to Australia for higher education. At Global-Migrate we hire a dedicated team of MARA regulated consultants to advise those who might be interested in migrating to Australia to study. As we have been in business for over 15 years and work with all established education institutions in Australia we are in a postion to help you secure a place at the University, School or College of your choice. We are so confident of securing this visa for you that we offer you a No Visa No Fee policy for this application.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAustralia has a reputation for having some of the world’s leading education institutions. By Joining the thousands of satisfied international students studying in Australia, you will experience a unique kind of education.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost you will need to be enrolled by a recognised university in Australia, which we can help you with. Once you have an acceptance letter you would be able to make an application for a study visa provided you have enough finances to cover your tuition fee and your cost of living for the entire period of your stay.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nWe also provide a complete relocation service from Airport transfers to finding an accomodation and opening bank accounts to name a few\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nYour student visa will list the conditions that apply specifically to you. It is important to comply with your visa conditions to avoid visa cancellation.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThere many different types of study visas available.\r\n\r\n</p><h4>How to apply</h4>\r\nTo find out more please contact our Australian team on +44 (0)207 9934762 or use our free assessment tool below\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n', 'Australia Study Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '59-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:31:58', '2014-03-07 07:31:58', '', 59, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/59-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(357, 1, '2014-03-07 09:46:06', '2014-03-07 09:46:06', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  <span style="font-size:16px; font-family:''Trebuchet MS''; color:blue;">Thinking of moving to Australia? Don’t think, do it, as this would be one of the best decisions you would ever make …</span><br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n                  Well if you have, then Global-Migrate is here to assist. As migration agents we completely understand that migration to Australia is not just a lengthy process but also complicated. However, with many years or practice and experience we fully understand the standard of work required in your application process for a successful application. It’s not just about complying with all the regulations, it’s as much about presenting the facts of your case in the right way to ensure that your application gets through the system the first time you apply. As a company that hires MARA registered agents we are bound by a strict code of conduct for your protection <a style="color:blue" href="https://www.mara.gov.au/Code-of-Conduct/Code-of-Conduct/default.aspx">(MARA Code of Conduct)</a><br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n                  Covering a total area of 7.69 million square kilometers, mainland Australia is the world’s largest island &ndash; but smallest continent.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAustralia is also the only continent that is governed as a single country. It is sometimes informally referred to as an ‘island’ continent, surrounded by oceans.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nMost Australians are immigrants or the descendants of immigrants who arrived during the past two hundred years from more than 200 countries. The most commonly spoken language in Australia is English, and the most commonly practiced religion is Christianity, although foreign languages and other religions are also common.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nAustralian Immigration can be quite a complex and a time consuming process, therefore, we strongly advise you to seek assistance from people in the know how. A regulated consultancy who hires a MARA agent like us is definitely a good option. This reduces the chance of a rejection in your visa application and most definitely is a wise decision if you are deciding to make a life changing decision for a better future for you and your family.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nYou may apply for immigration to Australia via many different routes. You can be a skilled worker whose occupation might be in demand or you might be a school or college leaver who wants to migrate to Australia and get work experience.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nGlobal-Migrate specialises in all Australian Skilled Migration, Work Permits, Study Visas and Working Holiday Visas for Australia. We hire a team of MARA regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian Government to give advice and assist someone like you.<br>\r\n </p><div class="more2"><a class="more" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment"></a> </div><br>\r\nThe most common and popular immigration routes for Australia are;\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="australia-partner-visa-australia-marriage-visa.html">Partner Visas</a></h3>\r\nThere are many different types of partner visa to Australia. These include the Spouse Partner Visa, the Defacto Partner Visa, the Interdependent Partner Visa and the Prospective Marriage Partner Visa.<p></p>\r\n<p></p><h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="australian-family-visa.html">Family Visas</a></h3>\r\nFamily Migration is one of the most common and popular way of entering Australia legally. There are a number of different types of applications you can apply for under this category. You may qualify if you have a family member who is a citizen of Australia. This could be your parents or your children or even a partner who you would like to go and settle with. Whatever the situation, if you have a family member who is a citizen or a permanent resident of Australia, we can help. So why don''t you call our specialist Australian immigration team now on +44 (0)2079934762<p></p>\r\n<p></p><h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-189.html">Skilled Independent Visa - (Subclass 189)</a></h3>\r\nThe Skilled Independent visa is a points-based application. To qualify for the independant visa, you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements, you will be eligible for this visa. This visa is without a doubt the most desired route of immigration to Australia, however, you need to score very high points to be able to apply for this visa. This is an independent application which means no state, or territory will sponsor you and you need to score the required points without having to claim any bonus points for sponsorship. Although the application takes between 12 - 16 months, but once approved you are a permanent resident in Australia and you have the flexibility to settle anywhere in Australia. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian Skilled independent immigration process. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.<p></p>\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-190.html">Skilled Nominated Visa &ndash; (Subclass 190)</a></h3>\r\nThe Skilled Sponsored visa is a points-based application. To qualify for this type of visa you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements you may be eligible for this visa. Once approved you become a permanent resident of Australia from day one however you have a restriction to your stay in Australia, where you need to live in the region that sponsors your occupation for at least 24 months. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian sponsored immigration. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-489.html">Skilled Nominated or Sponsored Visa &ndash; (Subclass 489)</a></h3>\r\nThe Skilled Regional Sponsored visa is initially based on meeting a point score. To qualify for this visa, you must first pass basic requirements. You get points for your age, English competence, training, work experience and having an eligible relative (or a state) able to sponsor you. Once you meet these requirements, you may be eligible for this type of visa. This is initially a 3 year visa sponsored by a state. You may apply for permanent residency after 2 years if you meet the criteria. For this application your occupation MUST be nominated by a state. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian state sponsored immigration. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><a style="color:#0033CC" href="australia-work-holiday-visa.html">Working Holiday Visa</a></h3>\r\nThis visa is for people aged 18 to 30 years of age, who are interested in a working holiday of up to 12 months in Australia. You can extend this visa automatically after the 12 months by another 1 year.\r\n\r\nIf you are granted this visa you can, enter Australia within 12 months of grant, leave and re-enter Australia any number of times while the visa is valid and study for up to four months if you wish\r\n\r\nTo get more information on any of the above visa either call us on +44 (0)207 9934762 or click on the desired visa option on the left.\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n    ', 'Australia Immigration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 09:46:06', '2014-03-07 09:46:06', '', 77, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/77-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(289, 1, '2014-03-07 07:32:29', '2014-03-07 07:32:29', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                  A tourist visa is one of the most popular visas for Australia. There are many categories of visitors. A visitor is someone who generally intends to be in Australia for a short period, for example, to visit friends and family, to do business, to do a short course of study, to have private medical treatment. The information given here aims to deal with the various categories of visitors coming to Australia.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nIn general, you must show that:\r\n</p><ul>\r\n<li> you want to visit Australia for no more than six months;</li>\r\n<li> you intend to leave at the end of your visit;</li>\r\n<li>you have enough money to support yourself during your stay</li>\r\n<li> you do not intend to take paid or unpaid employment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe different types of tourist visas for Australia are:\r\n<h4>ETA (Visitor) (Subclass 976)</h4>\r\nAn electronically stored authority for short-term visits to Australia of up to 3 months. Available to passport holders from a number of countries and regions, who are outside Australia.\r\n\r\n<h4>eVisitors (Subclass 651)</h4>\r\nAn electronically stored authority for visits to Australia for tourism or business purposes for up to three months. Available to passport holders from the European Union and a number of other European countries, who are outside Australia.\r\n\r\n<h4>Tourist visa (Subclass 676)</h4>\r\nA temporary visa allowing a stay in Australia of up to three or six or 12 months. Applicants can apply from both outside and in Australia. Some tourists are eligible to lodge an online application for an e676 Tourist visa.\r\n\r\n<h4>Sponsored Family Visitor visa (Subclass 679)</h4>\r\nFor people seeking to visit family in Australia for a stay period of up to 12 months. Formal sponsorship by an Australian citizen or permanent resident is required.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nTo find out more or to apply for a successful tourist visa for Australia please call us on +44 (0) 207 9934762\r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n', 'Australia Tourist Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '63-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:32:29', '2014-03-07 07:32:29', '', 63, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/63-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
