(323, 1, '2014-03-07 07:46:33', '2014-03-07 07:46:33', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                 <p>\r\nSkilled migrant visa is an option for highly skilled people to immigrate to Australia on a permanent basis. Skilled migrants have always been welcome in most countries but Australia offers more rewarding opportunities in the form of high salaries, career growth and stability than any other country. Get in touch with Global Migrate now to find out if you qualify as a skilled migrant for Australia\r\n<br><br>\r\nSkilled migrants have three different options for Australia ;\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n</p><h4>Skilled Independent Visa - (Subclass 189)</h4>\r\n<p>The Skilled Independent visa is a points-based application. To qualify for the independent visa, you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements, you will be eligible for this visa. This visa is without a doubt the most desired route of immigration to Australia; however, you need to score very high points to be able to apply for this visa. This is an independent application which means no state, or territory will sponsor you and you need to score the required points without having to claim any bonus points for sponsorship.<br>\r\n<strong><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-189.html">Read More...</a></strong></p>\r\n<h4>Skilled Nominated Visa &ndash; (Subclass 190)</h4>\r\n<p>The Skilled Sponsored visa is a points-based application. To qualify for this type of visa you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements you may be eligible for this visa. Once approved you become a permanent resident of Australia from day one however you have a restriction to your stay in Australia, where you need to live in the region that sponsors your occupation for at least 24 months.<br>\r\n<strong><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-190.html">Read More...</a></strong></p>\r\n<h4>Skilled Nominated or Sponsored Visa &ndash; (Subclass 489) </h4>\r\n<p>The Skilled Regional Sponsored visa is initially based on meeting a point score. To qualify for this visa, you must first pass basic requirements. You get points for your age, English competence, training, work experience and having an eligible relative (or a state) able to sponsor you. Once you meet these requirements, you may be eligible for this type of visa. This is initially a 3 year visa sponsored by a state.<br>\r\n<strong><a style="color:#0033CC" href="skilled-subclass-489.html">Read More... </a></strong></p>\r\n                  <p></p> \r\n                  <p></p> </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n    ', 'Skilled Migrant Visa Australia', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '73-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:46:33', '2014-03-07 07:46:33', '', 73, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/73-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(324, 1, '2014-03-07 07:46:58', '2014-03-07 07:46:58', '            <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>\r\n                Australia offers skilled workers permanent residency under the points-based visa system. One of these visa types is the Skilled Regional Sponsored, or subclass 489, visa. Like the other visas in this system, you must demonstrate knowledge of the English language, and you must be under 50 years old.<br><br>\r\nGlobal-Migrate’s MARA regulated immigration advisors have helped many people with their skilled migrant visas. To receive your free visa assessment, get in touch today. We can help determine in the subclass 489 visa is right for you.<br><br>\r\nTo qualify for this visa, you must also have sponsorship from a relative in Australia. The Skilled Regional visa is aimed at certain Designated Areas of Australia. Your family member must live in one of these areas. To find out what relatives can sponsor you, and where they must live, get in touch with Global-Migrate for the most up-to-date information.<br>\r\n <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> </a></p><div class="more"></div>\r\n <br>\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you can apply on the basis of a nomination from a participating state or territory government. For more information about this path, and how to get a nomination, call Global-Migrate’s advisors today.<br><br>\r\nOur consultants can also give you guidance about the application process. For the subclass 489 visa, you will need to first submit an expression of interest, in which you will need to give information about your occupation and your skill level. Global-Migrate can help you with your Expression of Interest, and can help you find out about what occupations are in demand in Australia.<br><br>\r\nThe 489 visa can be a great option for living and working in Australia. While you will need to stay in the specific area of your sponsorship or nomination during the first part of your visa, you will be eligible to apply for permanent residency after two years. When this is granted, you will be free to live and work in any part of Australia.<br><br>\r\nThe Skilled Nominated or Sponsored Provisional Visa can be the ideal way for you to migrate to Australia. To find out more about this and other visas, and to find out the best choice for you, call Global-Migrate’s experienced advisors today.\r\n\r\n\r\n                  <p></p>\r\n                   </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n              <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        ', 'Skilled-Nominated or Sponsored (Provisional)-(subclass 489) Visa', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '53-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:46:58', '2014-03-07 07:46:58', '', 53, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/53-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(325, 1, '2014-03-07 07:48:58', '2014-03-07 07:48:58', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2"><p>\r\n                 If you are a Canadian citizen or permanent resident, you may be able to sponsor certain family members to join you in Canada. These family members include spouses, partners, and children.<br><br>\r\nTo find out if you are eligible to sponsor family members, use Global-Migrate’s free initial assessment. We’ll help you determine if you are able to sponsor family members, and what you’ll need to do to have your family join you in Canada.<br><br>\r\nFor family members to join you in Canada, you’ll need to do a two-part process. Both parts must be completed and submitted at the same time.<br><br>\r\nThe first part is your application to be a sponsor. There are different applications depending on whether your family members are already in Canada, or if they are currently living outside of Canada. Global-Migrate can help you determine which type of application you will need to make.<br><br>\r\nThe second half of the process is your family member’s application for permanent residence. Global-Migrate has helped many families with their Canadian migration, and we have a very high success rate. Our trained advisors are able to help you with each part of the complex and often confusing process.<br><br>\r\nFamily sponsorship is currently limited to spouses, partners, and children. For Canadian immigration purposes, spouses include those who have a legitimate marriage, including same-sex marriages. Partners include common-law and conjugal partners, in either different-sex or same-sex relationships. <br><br>\r\nFor applications made after 25 October 2012, you will need to live together for two years from the day your partner’s permanent residency was granted. There are some exceptions to this new rule, and Global-Migrate’s team of advisors can give you the most up-to-date information.\r\nGlobal-Migrate can also help you find out whether your children or other dependents under the age of 18 are eligible to be sponsored. We can also help you with an application for a Parent or Grandparent Super Visa, which can allow certain older relatives to visit you in Canada for extended stays.<br><br>\r\nIf you want to know more about how your family can join you in Canada, get in touch with Global-Migrate’s team of ICCRC registered immigration advisors today!<br><br>\r\n\r\n					 </p>\r\n                   </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> <div class="more"></div></a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10">&nbsp;</td> \r\n            <td width="20">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'Sponsor Your Family', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '119-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 07:48:58', '2014-03-07 07:48:58', '', 119, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/119-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
