(405, 1, '2014-03-07 13:48:48', '2014-03-07 13:48:48', '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                \r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="normalTxt" colspan="2">\r\n                  <p>Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR) allows you to migrate to Britain permanently. It is often referred to as permanent UK residency. As part of this you gain settled status and can apply for British citizenship via <a href="british-citizenship.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#274789;">naturalisation</span></a>.</p>\r\n<p>An application for permanent residency in the UK can be made by people who have previously been successful in applying for a UK visa in Britain in a category leading to settlement. These categories will say if they are or are not eligible and counted towards the right to remain.</p>\r\n<p>Global-Migrate can help you to obtain anything from a short-term visit visa through to long-term residency and citizenship. We handle everything and anything to do with UK immigration. You can find out whether you qualify by completing our online Indefinite Leave to Remain assessment form today.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ILR Benefits</strong><br><br>\r\nA permanent resident visa for Great Britain has no time limit imposed upon it, and whereas a work permit would depend upon a specific offer of employment, there are no immigration related restrictions upon the type of work or business a person with a permanent UK resident status may undertake on arrival.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ILR Duration</strong><br><br>\r\nThere is no time limit; however, it is important to note that holders should not spend periods of more than two years outside of the United Kingdom. A long-term UK resident should consider the United Kingdom as home and spending only short periods of time in Britain may lead to the loss of ILR.<br>\r\nA person with ILR may be eligible to apply for British Naturalisation as a UK citizen, provided they meet the requirements for <a href="british-citizenship.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#274789;">British citizenship</span></a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong><br><br>\r\nThe applicant must have a settled status in Britain. This usually means that the candidate must have been resident in Great Britain on the same visa class for at least four years. The only exception to this is for people on marriage visas or De Facto visas, who only require two years and for periods of exceptionally long-term residency (10 years legal, or 14 years as a combination of illegal and legal residency).</p>\r\n<p>Ancestry and being an EU National can be a way in, as can marriage. All applicants have to demonstrate sufficient understanding of the English language and the English way of life in order to qualify.</p>\r\n<p>Global-Migrate can make an application for you Indefinite Leave to Remain (Also known as the ILR) using one of our premium services, which means that you will have your passport back within 24 hours. Certain categories cannot be applied for using the premium services, for e.g. ILR through <a href="long-term-residency-visa.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color:#274789;">long residency</span></a> (10 years legal stay in the UK), partner of an EEA national or an EEA national who has spent 5 years in the UK</p>\r\n<p>The UKBA might not make a decision within 24 hours in some cases even if you opt for the premium service. This will depend on the individuals application.</p>\r\n<p>An application for ILR can only be made 28 days prior to you becoming eligible for the application.</p>\r\n<p>Do you think you qualify for your ILR? To find out more please call us directly on +44 (0)207 9934762 or use our FREE assessment form.</p> <p></p>\r\n                  </td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td align="left">  <a class="more" title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php"> </a></td>\r\n                  <td align="right"><table width="157" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0">\r\n          <tbody><tr>\r\n             <td width="10"> </td> \r\n            <td width="20"> </td>\r\n            <td width="36"></td>\r\n            <td width="34"></td>\r\n            <td width="41"></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </tbody></table></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>', 'UK ILR Services', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '157-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-07 13:48:48', '2014-03-07 13:48:48', '', 157, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/157-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
