(482, 1, '2014-03-28 11:43:59', '2014-03-28 11:43:59', '<img alt="" src="http://health.info.yorku.ca/files/2014/02/future-student-image.jpg" />\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class="normalTxt" colspan="2" valign="top">Nova Scotia, in Canada is one of the three Maritime provinces and constitutes one of the four Atlantic Canada provinces. Nova Scotia is the second-smallest province in Canada, The population as off 2011 was 921,727, making Nova Scotia the second-most-densely populated province in Canada.Nova Scotia establishes its own immigration requirements and selects immigrants who will adapt well to living there. It has a huge shortage for highly and semi skilled workers.The government strongly believes that Immigrants help make Nova Scotia a vibrant, dynamic society. - See more at: http://novascotiaimmigration.com/#sthash.ykiZn5fh.dpufThis Canadian skilled Migration program has 2 steps.<strong>STEP 1: APPLY TO THE NOVA SCOTIA NOMINEE PROGRAM</strong>\r\n\r\nif you have decided you want to live and work permanently in Nova Scotia, you must review the different NSNP streams to determine if you qualify. Global-Migrate can help you understand this process. You are eligible for a FREE assessment so why don''t you call our Canadian consultant''s on 0203 589 6791 to discuss your application.\r\n\r\n<strong>STEP 2: APPLY TO CITIZENSHIP AND IMMIGRATION CANADA FOR A PERMANENT RESIDENT VISA</strong>\r\n\r\nOnce you have applied for a nominee program with the help of Global-Migrate, within six (6) months of receiving your nominee certificate, you must apply to Citizenship and Immigration Canada (CIC) for your permanent resident visa. You, your spouse and dependents must meet requirements for medical, security and criminal admissibility, and in some cases you may be asked to go for an interview. CIC has the final authority to issue a permanent resident visa. As this is a very complex application Global-Migrate will be delighted to help you and your family migrate to Nova Scotia. With experienced caseworkers in our team we can make the journey for you very simple and stress free. After all this is a life changing decision and you want to get it right the first time?\r\n\r\nTo find out more about immigration to Canada visa the Nova Scotia Nominee Program please call us directly on 0203 589 6791</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="left"><a title="Start Your Free Visa Assessment" href="http://www.global-migrate.com/free-assessment.php">\r\n<div class="more"></div>\r\n</a></td>\r\n<td align="right">\r\n<table width="157" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="10"></td>\r\n<td width="20"></td>\r\n<td width="36"></td>\r\n<td width="34"></td>\r\n<td width="41"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Nova Scotia Skilled Immigration', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'nova-scotia-skilled-immigration', '', '', '2014-11-14 16:20:24', '2014-11-14 16:20:24', '', 0, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/?page_id=482', 0, 'page', '', 0),
