(516, 1, '2014-11-12 16:41:38', '2014-11-12 16:41:38', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class="normalTxt" colspan="2" valign="top"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: ''Trebuchet MS''; color: blue;">Thinking of moving to Australia? Don’t think, do it, as this would be one of the best decisions you would ever make …</span>\n\nWell if you have, then Global-Migrate is here to assist. As migration agents we completely understand that migration to Australia is not just a lengthy process but also complicated. However, with many years or practice and experience we fully understand the standard of work required in your application process for a successful application. It’s not just about complying with all the regulations, it’s as much about presenting the facts of your case in the right way to ensure that your application gets through the system the first time you apply. As a company that hires MARA registered agents we are bound by a strict code of conduct for your protection <a style="color: blue;" href="https://www.mara.gov.au/Code-of-Conduct/Code-of-Conduct/default.aspx">(MARA Code of Conduct)</a>\n\nCovering a total area of 7.69 million square kilometers, mainland Australia is the world’s largest island – but smallest continent.\n\nAustralia is also the only continent that is governed as a single country. It is sometimes informally referred to as an ‘island’ continent, surrounded by oceans.\n\nMost Australians are immigrants or the descendants of immigrants who arrived during the past two hundred years from more than 200 countries. The most commonly spoken language in Australia is English, and the most commonly practiced religion is Christianity, although foreign languages and other religions are also common.\n\nAustralian Immigration can be quite a complex and a time consuming process, therefore, we strongly advise you to seek assistance from people in the know how. A regulated consultancy who hires a MARA agent like us is definitely a good option. This reduces the chance of a rejection in your visa application and most definitely is a wise decision if you are deciding to make a life changing decision for a better future for you and your family.\n\nYou may apply for immigration to Australia via many different routes. You can be a skilled worker whose occupation might be in demand or you might be a school or college leaver who wants to migrate to Australia and get work experience.\n\nGlobal-Migrate specialises in all Australian Skilled Migration, Work Permits, Study Visas and Working Holiday Visas for Australia. We hire a team of MARA regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian Government to give advice and assist someone like you.\n<div class="more2"></div>\nThe most common and popular immigration routes for Australia are;\n<h3><a style="color: #0033cc;" href="australia-partner-visa-australia-marriage-visa.html">Partner Visas</a></h3>\nThere are many different types of partner visa to Australia. These include the Spouse Partner Visa, the Defacto Partner Visa, the Interdependent Partner Visa and the Prospective Marriage Partner Visa.\n<h3><a style="color: #0033cc;" href="australian-family-visa.html">Family Visas</a></h3>\nFamily Migration is one of the most common and popular way of entering Australia legally. There are a number of different types of applications you can apply for under this category. You may qualify if you have a family member who is a citizen of Australia. This could be your parents or your children or even a partner who you would like to go and settle with. Whatever the situation, if you have a family member who is a citizen or a permanent resident of Australia, we can help. So why don''t you call our specialist Australian immigration team now on +44 (0)2079934762\n<h3><a style="color: #0033cc;" href="skilled-subclass-189.html">Skilled Independent Visa - (Subclass 189)</a></h3>\nThe Skilled Independent visa is a points-based application. To qualify for the independant visa, you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements, you will be eligible for this visa. This visa is without a doubt the most desired route of immigration to Australia, however, you need to score very high points to be able to apply for this visa. This is an independent application which means no state, or territory will sponsor you and you need to score the required points without having to claim any bonus points for sponsorship. Although the application takes between 12 - 16 months, but once approved you are a permanent resident in Australia and you have the flexibility to settle anywhere in Australia. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian Skilled independent immigration process. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\n<h3><a style="color: #0033cc;" href="skilled-subclass-190.html">Skilled Nominated Visa – (Subclass 190)</a></h3>\nThe Skilled Sponsored visa is a points-based application. To qualify for this type of visa you must first meet basic requirements around your age, English competence, training and work experience. Once you meet these requirements you may be eligible for this visa. Once approved you become a permanent resident of Australia from day one however you have a restriction to your stay in Australia, where you need to live in the region that sponsors your occupation for at least 24 months. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian sponsored immigration. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\n<h3><a style="color: #0033cc;" href="skilled-subclass-489.html">Skilled Nominated or Sponsored Visa – (Subclass 489)</a></h3>\nThe Skilled Regional Sponsored visa is initially based on meeting a point score. To qualify for this visa, you must first pass basic requirements. You get points for your age, English competence, training, work experience and having an eligible relative (or a state) able to sponsor you. Once you meet these requirements, you may be eligible for this type of visa. This is initially a 3 year visa sponsored by a state. You may apply for permanent residency after 2 years if you meet the criteria. For this application your occupation MUST be nominated by a state. We at Global-Migrate specialise in the Australian state sponsored immigration. We have over 15 years of experience dealing with such applications. We have a specialist team of MARA (Migration Agents Registration Authority) regulated agents who are authorised by the Australian government to give advice and assist people with the complex Australian Immigration process.\n<h3><a style="color: #0033cc;" href="australia-work-holiday-visa.html">Working Holiday Visa</a></h3>\nThis visa is for people aged 18 to 30 years of age, who are interested in a working holiday of up to 12 months in Australia. You can extend this visa automatically after the 12 months by another 1 year.\n\nIf you are granted this visa you can, enter Australia within 12 months of grant, leave and re-enter Australia any number of times while the visa is valid and study for up to four months if you wish\n\nTo get more information on any of the above visa either call us on +44 (0)207 9934762 or click on the desired visa option on the left.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align="left"></td>\n<td align="right">\n<table width="157" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width="10"></td>\n<td width="20"></td>\n<td width="36"></td>\n<td width="34"></td>\n<td width="41"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'Australia Immigration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-11-12 16:41:38', '2014-11-12 16:41:38', '', 77, 'http://www.global-migrate.com/77-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
